Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(639,50)}听译、时间轴：刘巍然（学酥）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.62,0:00:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我想讨论的第二个思想实验叫\NThe second thought experiment that I want to discuss is called
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭将军问题\Nthe Byzantine generals problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.80,0:00:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在我讲解具体内容之前\NBefore I get into the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.62,0:00:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们先来讨论一下发音问题 到底是“ˈbɪzəntiːn”还是“baɪˈzæntaɪn”\Na question of pronunciation is it “ˈbɪzəntiːn” or “baɪˈzæntaɪn” generals?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.26,0:00:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,据我所知\NWell, so, as far as I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.28,0:00:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,标准英式英语的发音是“baɪˈzæntaɪn” \Nthe standard British pronunciation of this word is actually “baɪˈzæntaɪn”,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.72,0:00:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,而“ˈbɪzəntiːn”是美式英语发音\Nand “ˈbɪzəntiːn” is the American pronunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.78,0:00:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 在计算机领域 大部分人的读音是“bɪzənˈtiːn”\NHowever, in computing, it seems to be most common to use “bɪzənˈtiːn”.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.54,0:00:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 我这里也遵从习俗 把这个词发音为“bɪzənˈtiːn”\NAnd so, I'm just going to stick with the pronunciation “bɪzənˈtiːn”,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.88,0:00:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这也是计算机领域其他人常使用的发音\Nbecause that's what everyone else in computing seems to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.62,0:00:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭将军问题乍看起来与两将军问题很相似\NSo, the Byzantine generals problem is similar at first glance to the two generals problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.60,0:00:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这也是以将军率领军队打仗为背景描述的问题\Nthat is, again, we've got generals leading armies,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.78,0:00:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,军队同样希望进攻一个城市\Nagain, the armies want to attack a city.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个问题中 我们可能会有三支或者更多支军队\NIn this case, we might have three or more armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.72,0:00:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有多支军队\NWe might have any number of armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.82,0:00:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,和之前一样 将军通过信使完成通信\NAs before, the generals communicate by messenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,同样 军队需要商议出进攻日期\NAnd as before, the armies want to agree on the date of attack
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.30,0:01:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,保证军队可以同时发起进攻\Nso that to ensure that they attack at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.84,0:01:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,现在 我们在某个方面把问题简单化 但在另一个方面把问题复杂化\NNow, we make the problem easier in one way and harder in another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.20,0:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,简单化的部分如下 首先 我们假设消息通信过程是可靠的\NSo, easier, first of all, is we assume that messaging is reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个问题中 我们假设信使不会被抓获\NSo, in this case, we're going to assume messengers don't get captured,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.66,0:01:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,任何发送出去的消息一定会被相应的接收方所接收\Nbut any message that gets sent will actually be received by the appropriate recipient.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.82,0:01:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,复杂化的地方是 我们现在假设\NTo make the problem harder, we are now going to assume that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.32,0:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,有些将军是不忠诚的 他们是背叛者 他们是恶意的\Nsome of the generals are actually not loyal. They are traitors. They are malicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会尝试主动陷害其他将军\NThey are going to try to actively undermine the other generals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.38,0:01:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会撒谎 会欺骗\NSo, they are going to lie and deceive,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.18,0:01:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会按照任何他们期望的形式作出不端的行动\Nand generally misbehave in any sort of way as they wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.10,0:01:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他们甚至可能会共谋\NThey might even work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.96,0:01:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管如此 我们仍然希望\NAnd nevertheless, we want
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.78,0:01:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,诚实的将军们可以协商出向城市发起进攻的时间\Nthe honest generals to come to an agreement about the attack of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,让我通过一个例子来说明\NSo, let me give an example of the problem that might arise
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.90,0:01:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,当存在恶意将军时 会出现什么问题\Ndue to some generals being malicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.58,0:02:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,具体例子如下 将军1向将军2和将军3发送消息“进攻！”\NSo, here, in this example, general 1 sends a message “Attack!” to generals 2 and 3,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,给两位将军发送的消息都是“进攻！”\Nthe same message “Attack!”.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.40,0:02:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,将军3如愿收到了消息\NAnd general 3 receives that message as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.14,0:02:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,将军2收到了进攻消息\NGeneral 2 receives the attack message,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,他随后给将军3发送一条消息称“将军1说撤退！”\Nand then sends a message to general 3 saying “Retreat!”.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.78,0:02:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,将军2这里做的事情就是说谎\NSo, what general 2 here is doing is lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.06,0:02:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,将军2称将军1发送了一条撤退消息\NGeneral 2 claims that general 1 sent a retreat message
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.22,0:02:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但实际上 将军1发送了一条进攻消息\Nwhen in fact, general 1 sent an attack message.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.46,0:02:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 在这种情况下 将军2实施了恶意行为\NSo, in this case, here, general 2 is the one who is being malicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 从将军3的视角上看 他很难判断出到底发生了什么\NUnfortunately, from the point of general 3, it's not easy to tell what is actually happening
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.16,0:02:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因为从将军3的视角上看\Nbecause from the point of general 3,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.30,0:02:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,也有可能发生的是下图所描述的情况\Nwhat could have just this equally well happened is this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.70,0:02:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能是将军1向将军3发送了一条进攻消息\NSo, it could be that general 1 sent an attack message to 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.06,0:02:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,而将军1向将军2发送了一条撤退消息\NAnd general 1 sent a retreat message to 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.54,0:02:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上\NAnd general 2 is actually
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,将军2诚实地重复了将军1发来的撤退消息\Nfaithfully repeating that retreat message that it got from general 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:03:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在下图所示的情况下 将军2才是诚实的\NSo, in this case, in the lower case here, general 2 is being honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,因为将军2只是诚实报告了将军1发来的消息\Nbecause general 2 is just reporting honestly what general 1 said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.38,0:03:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,将军1实施了恶意行为\NAnd it's general 1 who is being malicious
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.34,0:03:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,将军1向将军2和将军3发送了相互矛盾的命令\Nby sending contradictory commands to generals 2 and 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,在将军3的视角下 我们面对的核心问题是\NSo, the core of the problem here from the point of view of general 3 is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.34,0:03:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,将军3无法区分这两个场景\Nit's impossible to tell the difference between these two scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.74,0:03:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,将军3无法知道\NAnd so, it's impossible for general 3 to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.06,0:03:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,到底是将军1作恶 还是将军2作恶\Nwhether general 1 is being malicious or whether general 2 is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.58,0:03:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,正如我前面所说 在节点可能说谎的场景下\NNow, given this scenario where nodes might lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.38,0:03:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭将军问题所要达成的目标是\Nthe Byzantine generals problem is that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.02,0:03:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望所有诚实的将军可以达成一致\Nwe want all of the honest generals to come to an agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.24,0:03:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,现在 我们面对的问题是\NSo now, the problem is that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.44,0:03:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,诚实的将军无法知道恶意将军会做些什么\Nthe honest generals don't know who the malicious generals are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.76,0:03:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们可以假设恶意将军的数量不会超过某个最大值\NBut we are going to assume some maximum number of generals being malicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.10,0:04:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以假设 一共有n位将军 其中最多有f位将军是恶意的\NSo, let's say that up to f generals are malicious out of n generals in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,诚实将军不知道哪些人是恶意将军\NThe honest generals don't know who the malicious ones are,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,但恶意将军知道其他恶意将军是谁\Nbut the malicious generals may know who the other malicious generals are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 他们甚至可以共同协作\NAnd so, they might actually even work together in some coordinated fashion
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,尝试欺骗和愚弄诚实将军\Nto try to deceive and trick the honest generals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.24,0:04:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管如此 我们要求诚实将军仍然可以协商出一个计划\NAnd nevertheless, our requirement is that the honest generals agree on a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.78,0:04:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能约束恶意将军必须使用某种计划来作恶\NSo, we can't get the malicious generals to agree on any part of the plan
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们假设恶意将军可以按照任意的方法实施恶意行为\Nbecause we're assuming that they might misbehave in arbitrary ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.10,0:04:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 我们不可能知道他们会按照什么策略实施恶意行为\NAnd so, it's impossible for us to make any statement about what they are going to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.84,0:04:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们可以允许让诚实将军按照一定的策略行动\Nbut we can make a statement about what the honest generals are going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.20,0:04:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,而最终的目的是让诚实将军可以在相同日期发起进攻\NAnd that is, what we want them to do is to all attack on the same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,根据问题启动时所面对的不同情况\NNow, there are several different variants of the Byzantine generals problem
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,可以构造出拜占庭将军问题的很多变种问题\Nthat vary in the details of how exactly it's set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,但对于一些变种问题 我们可以证明出一个通用结论\NBut a typical result that we can prove about some of these variants is that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.16,0:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们最多有f位恶意将军\Nif we have a maximum of f malicious generals,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,则我们总共至少需要3f+1位将军\Nthen we need at least 3f+1 generals in total
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,才能容忍f位将军实施恶意行为\Nin order to tolerate those f generals being malicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.40,0:05:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是说 恶意将军的数量必须小于将军总数量的1/3\Nthat is, less than 1/3 of the total number of generals can be malicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.06,0:05:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们有3位将军 其中1位将军是恶意的 则此问题无解\NSo, if we have 3 generals, and 1 is malicious, the problem is unsolvable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.72,0:05:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,为了能让系统容忍1位恶意将军 我们至少需要4位将军\NIn order to tolerate a system with 1 malicious general, we need at least 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.46,0:05:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是说 当f=1时 我们总计至少需要4位将军\Nthat is, f=1, we need at least 4 generals in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.94,0:05:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,3位是诚实的 1位是恶意的\NSo, 3 honest ones and 1 malicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.94,0:05:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们希望系统中包含2位可能的恶意将军\NIf we want a system in which 2 generals might be malicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.06,0:05:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们总计需要7位将军 5位诚实将军 2位恶意将军\Nwe actually need 7, so, 5 honest and 2 malicious generals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.54,0:05:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,如果假定我们可以使用密码学技术 则这个问题会相对简单一些\NNow, the problem becomes somewhat easier if we assume that we can use cryptography.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.94,0:05:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会在这门课程中讲解用具体怎么使用密码学解决此问题\NAnd so, I won't go into the details of that in this course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.18,0:05:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在下一年的安全课程和密码学课程中\NThere's more detail on this in the security course and in the cryptography course
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.78,0:05:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,大家会了解具体细节\Nthat you will have next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.14,0:06:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,简述一下大致的方法 我们可以使用一个叫数字签名的技术\NBut what we can do here is use something called a digital signature,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一种消息形式 此消息形式可以证明\Nwhich is a form of message in which it can be proved that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,特定的消息一定是特定的参与方发送的\Na certain party sent a certain message.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.50,0:06:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,来看前面我给出的例子\NAnd so, in this case, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.02,0:06:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,数字签名允许将军2向将军3证明\Nit would allow general 2 to prove what a command general 1 sent to general 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我发送的就是将军1发送给将军2的消息\Nand prove that to general 3 in a way that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.92,0:06:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这样一来 将军3会相信将军2是诚实的\Ngeneral 3 would be convinced that general 2 really is honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,密码学会提供一定的帮助\NSo, cryptography does help,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.66,0:06:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,但密码学无法让拜占庭将军问题变成一个简单问题\Nbut it doesn't make the Byzantine generals problems magically simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.58,0:06:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,即使假定我们可以使用密码学 拜占庭将军问题仍然是一个很困难的问题\NSo, even if we do assume that we can use cryptography, the problem remains difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.16,0:06:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能会问：这个问题和实际场景有什么联系吗？\NSo, is this at all of practical relevance? You might ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.06,0:06:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把这个问题引入到前面已经多次提到的一个实际问题中\NSo, let's adapt this earlier example that we've had a few times now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,即引入到在线商店和支付服务问题\Nof the online shop and the payment service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.46,0:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个场景下 我们让客户作为第三个参与方\NAnd let's take, in this case, the customer as a third party in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,这样一来 我们就在商店、支付服务、客户之间\NSo, we have this kind of three-way relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.38,0:06:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,构建了一个三角关系\Nbetween the shop, the payment service, and the customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望这三个参与方\NAnd we want all three of these parties
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.20,0:07:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,可以对交易状态或订单状态达成一致\Nto agree on the status of a transaction, or the status of an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.50,0:07:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望在线商店发货之前已经确认\NSo, we want the online shop to ship the goods only if
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.50,0:07:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,支付服务已经处理完了支付过程\Nit agrees with the payment service that the payment actually happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,且客户已经为商品下单\Nand if the customer actually agreed that they did actually order this thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.58,0:07:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,客户希望确认自己确实用信用卡支付了约定好的金额 等等\Nand the customer agrees on the amount that was charged the card, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.88,0:07:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 所有参与方都需要达成一致\NSo, all of these parties need to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.76,0:07:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在实际生活中\NAnd in real life,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.28,0:07:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,三个参与方的信任关系可能会变得非常复杂\Nthe trust relationships between these three parties might be quite complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.38,0:07:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,如果从在线商店的角度考虑这个问题\NSo, if you think about it from the perspective of the online shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.94,0:07:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,如果存在某种方法\Nif there was some way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,使客户可以在不需要支付费用的条件下购买商品\Nhow people could order goods from an online shop without paying for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以想象到 骗子们就会趋之若鹜\Nyou can imagine that fraudsters would be using that pretty quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.96,0:07:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会在不完成支付的前提下 给所有昂贵的商品下单\Nand they would be ordering all sorts of expensive things without paying for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在线商店不希望发生这样的事情\NAnd so, the online shop would not be happy then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:07:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 从在线商店的角度看\NSo, from the point of view of the online shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.22,0:07:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在线商店需要假定客户可能存在恶意行为\Nthe customer needs to be treated as potentially malicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.54,0:07:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,因为如果盲目信任客户\Nbecause if the customer was just blindly trusted,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.02,0:08:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,那客户就可以实施上述欺骗行为\Nthen they might start doing fraudulent activity like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.20,0:08:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 在线商店和客户之间存在不信任的关系\NSo, in that case, we do have this kind of untrusting relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.90,0:08:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在线商店和支付服务的信任关系又如何呢？\NWhat about the online shop and the payment service, the relationship?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.38,0:08:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以想象到 支付服务可能不那么信任在线商店\NWell, you can imagine maybe the payment service doesn't quite trust the online shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.88,0:08:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,否则 某些人可能会开设一个诈骗在线商店\Nbecause otherwise, someone might set up a fraudulent online shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.00,0:08:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,用偷来的信用卡号码尝试交易\Nuse, say, stolen credit card numbers, to try and process transactions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.10,0:08:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在不发送任何商品的条件下收钱\Nand get money without actually shipping any real goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.04,0:08:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下 可能支付服务不能完全信任在线商店\NSo, in that case, probably the payment service doesn't fully trust the online shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但在线商店可能会信任支付服务\NBut maybe the shop does trust the payment service.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.44,0:08:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 这里还存在非平衡的信任关系\NSo, it might be this kind of asymmetric relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.22,0:08:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,正如大家所看到的 现实生活中的信任关系可能会非常复杂\NSo, as you can see here, the trust relationships in real life get rather complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.74,0:08:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,很多场景下都会出现一个参与方不信任另一个参与方的情况\NYou do end up in these situations where one party does not trust another party.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.66,0:08:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管如此 他们仍然希望一起搞定某些事情\NAnd they nevertheless want to get something done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.12,0:08:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 从这个角度看 拜占庭行为在现实中是真实存在的\NAnd so, in that sense, Byzantine behavior is real and practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.30,0:09:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,很显然 拜占庭将军问题对此类场景进行了高度的简化\NThe Byzantine generals problem is of course a simplification of this kind of scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.62,0:09:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,举例来说 拜占庭将军问题认为所有将军的信任关系是平等的\Nbecause it's treating all of the generals as symmetric, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.18,0:09:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管是一个简化版问题 拜占庭将军问题仍然是一个很好的出发点\NBut nevertheless, the Byzantine generals problem is a useful starting point
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.26,0:09:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,用于研究参与方不能相互信任的一类场景\Nfor studying these kind of situations in which the participants don't fully trust each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.74,0:09:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在我结束拜占庭将军问题的介绍之前\NSo, before I wrap up about the Byzantine generals problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我还想讲个和历史相关的题外话\None more little historical digression,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.34,0:09:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能会好奇 为什么把这个问题称为“拜占庭”将军问题？\Nyou might be wondering where the name Byzantine comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.72,0:09:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这个问题来自于拜占庭帝国\NSo, this comes from the Byzantine empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.02,0:09:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭帝国也称东罗马帝国\Nwhich also known as Byzantium, the former east Roman empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.76,0:09:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭帝国是罗马帝国覆灭后东侧部分所形成的帝国\Nwhich after the collapse of the Roman empire, this was the eastern part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.86,0:09:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭帝国的首都是君士坦丁堡 这个城市之前就叫拜占庭\NAnd its capital city was Constantinople, which was formerly known as Byzantium,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.38,0:09:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这个城市现在是位于土耳其的伊斯坦布尔\Nwhich is now where Istanbul is located in Turkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.96,0:09:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在二十世纪初 出于某些原因\NAnd so, for some reason in the early 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,人们开始用“拜占庭”这个术语\NI think the term Byzantine became used
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.80,0:10:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,来描述极为复杂的场景\Nin order to describe scenarios where things are excessively complicated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.44,0:10:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,或者描述非常官僚的场景 乃至潜在的不正当问题\Nor incredibly bureaucratic, or potentially even devious,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.70,0:10:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,例如用来描述税收立法等事件\Nfor example, tax legislation or these kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.32,0:10:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,目前还不完全清楚为什么会使用“拜占庭”这个术语描述此类问题\NNot entirely sure why that meaning of Byzantine occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.54,0:10:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,因为没有历史证据表明\Nbecause there's no historical evidence really that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.28,0:10:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,拜占庭帝国与其他帝国相比有过更恶意或者更诚实的行为\Nthe Byzantine empire was any more or less malicious than any other empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.20,0:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 这就是“拜占庭”这个术语的由来\NBut anyway, that's where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.92,0:10:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,人们很早就开始使用“拜占庭”这个术语了\NSo, the term Byzantine had this meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.04,0:10:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在计算机领域引入这个术语之前 人们就开始使用“拜占庭”这个术语了\Nlong before it was used in the context of computing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.50,0:10:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 使用“拜占庭”与计算机领域无关\NSo, it is outside of computing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.70,0:10:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,人们早就开始使用“拜占庭”这个术语了\NIt has had that meaning for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是拜占庭将军问题的全部内容\NSo, that's all on the Byzantine generals problem for now.
